commit_message:
Make deployed_server_prepare.sh compatible with newton

In 619bbe8bdc433a8c170ec910a61144b30a4ab3c8 we broke stable/newton.
This change assumes we only have a single controller role on newton,
because that is the only jobs we have there.

Change-Id: I6ac99de5c2a9f3c8e258027a1edbfeffa80cd6b3
Closes-Bug: 1712436

commit_message:
HAProxy: Make certmonger bundle the cert and key on renewal

the postsave command is ran by certmonger when a certificate is
requested (which will happen on certificate renewal). The previous
command given didn't take into account the file that haproxy expects,
which is a bundled PEM file with both the certificate and the key. Thus,
certmonger would have never generated a new bundle that haproxy would
use, resulting in haproxy always having an old bundle after certificate
expiration.

This fixes that.

Change-Id: Idb650d35f56abaf6a17e17794a068dd5933e6a62
Closes-Bug: #1712514

commit_message:
Fix panko port to match tht

In templates we use 13977 as the port for panko. The
old 13779 is reserved for trove so it conflicts.

Closes-bug: #1712566

Change-Id: I77444199eef6c2b9abbd819829b4fea2d698e2db
(cherry picked from commit 5064677dda8e4f140df6d024089e95afe11a91f1)

Support for Dell EMC Unity Manila Driver

This changes adds Dell EMC Unity backend as composable service
and matches the tripleo-heat-templates.

Implements: blueprint dellemc-unity-manila

[{'created': '2017-08-25 16:21:09.000000000', 'message': 'Do not try to inject repo into IPA image if we dont fetch it

When adding support to inject changes into the IPA image, we missed
a check for whether we are building images rather than fetching them.

This causes the jobs which build images to fail because they try to
modify an image we did not fetch.

Change-Id: Ife155e904a3118fb5b44419845e8fe321ea11e62
Closes-Bug: 1713079
'}]
commit_message:
Do not try to inject repo into IPA image if we dont fetch it

When adding support to inject changes into the IPA image, we missed
a check for whether we are building images rather than fetching them.

This causes the jobs which build images to fail because they try to
modify an image we did not fetch.

Change-Id: Ife155e904a3118fb5b44419845e8fe321ea11e62
Closes-Bug: 1713079

commit_message:
Enable some off-by-default checks

Some of the available checks are disabled by default, like:
[H106] Do not put vim configuration in source files
[H203] Use assertIs(Not)None to check for None
[H904] Delay string interpolations at logging calls

Change-Id: Iff0835a68cea4b1d57407829632c5a903810aafd

commit_message:
Handle failure of carrier check in configure_safe_defaults()

Configure_safe_defaults() should handle carrier check failures
in the same way as the change that was made to
dhcp-all-interfaces.sh in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/419527/.
That is, it should ignore failures when cat'ing the carrier file.

Change-Id: I100a40835d0ccecee9b4851aae6366c6ab4813a5
Closes-Bug: 1712687

subject: Include docker.yaml and docker-ha.yaml by default
revisions:
[{'created': '2017-08-26 14:30:25.000000000', 'message': 'Include docker.yaml and docker-ha.yaml by default

This patches in some custom (downstream only for now) code
that injects the docker.yaml and docker-ha.yaml
tripleo-heat-template environment files by default into the
default plan. This should ensure that both the CLI/UI default
to using docker and docker-ha for installs and updates.

Related BZ:
  https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1466744

Change-Id: Ib42e97d9c91ad28280291d1438fb0c055635c33c
'}]
commit_message:
Include docker.yaml and docker-ha.yaml by default

This patches in some custom (downstream only for now) code
that injects the docker.yaml and docker-ha.yaml
tripleo-heat-template environment files by default into the
default plan. This should ensure that both the CLI/UI default
to using docker and docker-ha for installs and updates.

Related BZ:
  https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1466744

Change-Id: Ib42e97d9c91ad28280291d1438fb0c055635c33c

commit_message:
Don't disable satellite repo after registration

Previously the rhel registration script disabled the satellite repo
after installing packages from it.  This means those packages will
never be updated, which is not desirable from a long-term
maintenance perspective.

I believe this behavior is a holdover from the dib registration
script, where we don't want to leave repos enabled because the
image may be deployed many times and each instance needs to be
re-registered.  In t-h-t we don't have that problem because the
script only runs at deploy time so it's okay and desirable to leave
the repos enabled.

Change-Id: I5d760467b458d90d74507a55effc49b71d22eaa3
Closes-Bug: 1673116
(cherry picked from commit 551baca688449f6f7f798577229cae39abbe6107)

commit_message:
doc migration: new directory layout

This patch introduces a new directory layout
in doc/source in conformance with the OpenStack
manuals project migration spec [1], moves the
existing content in manila/doc/source into the
new directories, and adjusts index files accordingly.

This is the first step in the migration process
as outlined in the spec.

[1] https://specs.openstack.org/openstack/docs-specs/specs/pike/os-manuals-migration.html

Partial-Bug: #1706181
Needed-By: Iac9a0180a8b1a45f6f1d84020c6d15f457ad92bf
Depends-On: I92cc896bbd505d10c9dc7101bacb4caedf43da8f
Depends-On: Ia750cb049c0f53a234ea70ce1f2bbbb7a2aa9454

Change-Id: I9c378a188f9009a82100f5488a936d43536bd5b6

commit_message:
doc migration: openstackdocstheme

This patch transitions to the openstackdocs theme from
oslosphinx in accord with the OpenStack manuals project
migration spec [1].

[1] https://specs.openstack.org/openstack/docs-specs/specs/pike/os-manuals-migration.html

Change-Id: I92cc896bbd505d10c9dc7101bacb4caedf43da8f
Partial-Bug: #1706181
Needed-By: I9c378a188f9009a82100f5488a936d43536bd5b6
Depends-On: Ia750cb049c0f53a234ea70ce1f2bbbb7a2aa9454

commit_message:
doc-migration: new directory layout

This patch introduces a new directory layout
in doc/source in conformance with the OpenStack
manuals project migration spec [1], moves the
existing content in manila/doc/source into the
new directories, and adjusts index files accordingly.

This is the first step in the migration process
as outlined in the spec.

[1] https://specs.openstack.org/openstack/docs-specs/specs/pike/os-manuals-migration.html

Closes-Bug: #1706181
Change-Id: I8964d066bb838fabbe94239ac108bff884c6ff76
Depends-On: I72be6303f9be77c0461eaacbc61bad8372546fb5
Depends-On: Ia750cb049c0f53a234ea70ce1f2bbbb7a2aa9454

commit_message:
Add enable_haproxy to globals.yml

Update comments and add enable_haproxy to let helpinners know how
to set kolla_internal_vip_address and deploy AIO OpenStack without
haproxy correctly.

As a beginner in kolla-ansible, current comments for
kolla_internal_vip_address let me belive that if I set it to my eth0 ip,
kolla-ansible will help deploy an AIO OpenStack without haproxy. But in
fact it throws an error, I get the right way after searching IRC log.

commit_message:
playbooks: os-swift-install: Use correct group name on openSUSE

The syslog user on openSUSE belongs to the 'users' group.

Change-Id: I82bbb2fcdc0fe57f52a812989b25fa16b94bfe68

commit_message:
group_vars: all: Replace spaces with underscores in distro repository

This is similar to I0966786226d3f534a7f326d9df2cd73e7e3749dd
ansible_distribution may return a string with spaces such as "openSUSE
Leap" so we need to replace the space with underscore in order to create a
more sensible repo name for the distro.

Change-Id: If653232b1bc51a3429875bc21ea88dba594423df

commit_message:
Check for lxc-ls/paths before collecting logs

The ansible-hardening gate doesn't have an /openstack/logs
directory nor does it have the lxc-ls executable. This patch
checks for both of those before collecting logs.

This patch is currently blocking the ansible-hardening gate.

Change-Id: Ic4ea169908fec86623dbe91859ec524e48683ab7

commit_message:
Set serial to 100% for nova_compute

When running serialized nova-compute install, the compute nodes won't have
all the ssh key. This patch ensure we have a working default setting.

Change-Id: I2665b189e3c0dda2d9663705b157d85a7d662a61

commit_message:
Add auto-generated CLI reference

The Ironic OSC plugin CLI was not being fully documented.

This patch enables an auto-generated CLI reference for the OSC plugin.

Note: There is a formatting issue with required arguments that include a
hyphen.  This has been opened as a bug [1].

[1] https://bugs.launchpad.net/python-cliff/+bug/1712612

Closes-Bug: #1712099
Change-Id: I541214f3b3bab9af0ae79c8055dfa1f151560b21

commit_message:
Appoint Kota TSUYUZAKI as Storlets PTL for Queens

Nobody self-nominated in time to become the Storlets PTL for the
Queens cycle, therefore the TC must appoint someone or disband
the project team.

The Pike PTL, Eran Rom, has moved to another organization and
can no longer dedicate time to Storlets. Kato Tsuyuzaki has been
the leading contributor for Storlets in the Pike cycle. He is
willing and able to fill the PTL position for the Queens cycle.

Change-Id: I4f1d0277ed34a94965e72a038aff6c84a14a0de8

commit_message:
Make cinder-manage service list to print full host

cinder service-list prints the full host when asked, cinder-manage
service-list just prints the short hostname, which is not usable.

123456-cinder01.foo-bar-1.baz.example.com@lvm vs 123456-cinder01

Update cinder-manage service list to match cinder service-list

Change-Id: Ie8b0b437aed0fe42a8938747b90a4e83e2c80c0d
Closes-Bug: #1712372

commit_message:
Repair immediate VF configuration for PCI SR-IOV

Change I71edc135432ab2193741c37ce977dd11172401e6 broke the host VF
configuration that set VF counts when the puppet is applied. This patch
re-adds the ensure => present property required for proper behavior.

Change-Id: Ibd18c4f3b7f0d8cee330f94f87e7ad4ea7ceeffb
Closes-Bug: #1712903

[{'created': '2017-08-24 04:20:23.000000000', 'message': 'Add image validation option

This patch adds whether or not set image validation option in configuration.
the image validation option is needed when user use docker registry for images.
for now, to validate  image on docker registry is impossible.
because docker engine is searching the image only  on docker hub.

commit_message:
Make image validation at API layer configurable

This patch adds whether or not set image validation option in configuration.

Change-Id: I477e0c5f2a3798e1c45e4c5a125987a02684f1be
Closes-Bug: #1709099

commit_message:
tests: bootstrap-host: Add ability to configure networking on SUSE

Add ability to configure networking on SUSE. Moreover, since the
ifup/ifdown network scripts are not destro specific, we rename them
and use them for SUSE as well.

Change-Id: I59c16e050b4774b88c397e404f82c176482a3b1f

- gate-tripleo-ci-centos-7-ovb-ha-oooq http://logs.openstack.org/65/472065/2/check-tripleo/gate-tripleo-ci-centos-7-ovb-ha-oooq/dab4b1b/ : SUCCESS in 2h 36m 26s'}, {'account_id': 21741, 'date': '2017-06-08 20:07:31.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

I think the structure (as used in the YAML file) is too complex.

If we stay with the current implemented structure (e.g. partitioning), one 'configuration' object should cope with only one volume group that 
* gets a list of block devices (physical volumes) to assemble the VG
* gets a list of logical volumes how it should be 'partitionied'.

In this case the input is a list of block devices (which were created by other elements) and the output is also a list of block devices (which can be used by other modules).

Having the structure as suggested implies, that it is possible to have multiple volume groups.  But then there is no need to have multiple top level 'lvm' configs."}, {'account_id': 7118, 'date': '2017-06-09 00:55:36.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

@andreas -- at this point there is more than enough for us to evaluate configuration in terms of samples & test-cases.  

i want to see how a sample configuration is actually parsed, testing of tree-to-graph equivalence, dumps of final configuration graphs (see DUMP_CONFIG_GRAPH) and at least a basic assert on some node ordering to assure ourselves the graph is in the right order.

There are test-case templates for all of this.  i don't mean a complete implementation.  but if we at least know that we transform a given configuration into a sane order-of-operations then we're about 90% of the way there."}, {'account_id': 7118, 'date': '2017-06-09 05:03:13.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 21741, 'date': '2017-06-09 05:21:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

@Ian: I think I understand your current approach.

Nevertheless: the structure of the config should be the same (or at least similar) as in the final solution.  My proposal is, not to have multiple VGs defined in one top level config object.

IMHO we should go for something like:

- lvm:
    base: "base"
    name: "base_name"
    vg_name: "log_vg"
    pvs:
      - options: ["--force"]
        base: root
    lvs:
      - name: "lv1"
        size: 100M
      - name: "lv2"
        size: 1G

This is cleaner and less work for the user (a user don't want to specify all these 'base' thingies over and over...)'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2017-06-09 05:46:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified-1

@Yolanda: I still don't see the point of having a 'vgs' as a list.  Maybe the top-name is irritating? Maybe we should rename it in 'vg' because it exactly defines one volume group?
Options to vg can then be placed directly under the top level element.

    - vg:
        vg_name: "log_vg"
        options: ["--some", "--options", "--to", "--vg"]
        pvs:
          - options: ["--force"]
            base: root
          - base: data1
          - base: data2
        lvs:
          - name: "lv1"
            size: 100M
          - name: "lv2"
            size: 1G

Please note that the top level element must not have a 'base' element (this was a copy & paste error I made in my last example). I don't like naming it "vg" because this is not what it is.
However, ahother use case came to my mind that will only be possible with Ian's data structure.
What about if we need to define several vg inside one partitioning? That is perfectly possible:
- define several pv, that point to different partitions on the disk
- define several vg, each one pointing to a different pv
- define several lv, each one pointing to a different vg

If we simplify too much, dropping the vg list, or removing the base fom lv, this cannot be possible. @Andreas - you made two points

One was about how this bunched a bunch of duplicate code in the the main function.  I believe the code layout now is better compartmentalised.  There is significant documentation on the way the nodes are built and where things are done inline.  I won't claim it's perfect, but I think it's as good a point to build on as any.

The other was about the config file format, and splitting it up.

At this point, the lvm: section isn't recursed, which kind-of breaks the strict tree model.  There is potential for this to be handled as the partitioning object does, with special-casing of this config section knowing which bits to recurse.  Personally I think this is of little benefit for the complexities it introduces, so I'm happy to leave this as future work.  There's plenty of templates and infrastructure for unit testing such a change (and avoiding regressions).

I also think that "LVM" is a global concept, and it's OK to have it as one config section, rather than have it split up and have volume-groups separate, or similar ideas.  I feel the vast majority of cases; a fairly simple group of volumes partitions; are covered by the existing case and the config files seem fine.  We have unit tests and sample configs for a single partition with vg's; multiple partitions with multiple vg's; and multiple paritions with vg's that span the partitions.  I'm not seeing anything that can't be expressed as is.

I certainly would like to hear more ideas on how we have to do this "dd" copy to avoid destroying the partitions on the cleanup path.  I have not been able to find a better way but I am very open to suggestions.

But overall, I think this is as good a place to start as any.  LGTM'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2017-08-24 07:42:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 17: Verified+1

commit_message:
LVM support for dib-block-device

This provides a basic LVM support to dib-block-device.

Co-Authored-By: Ian Wienand <iwienand@redhat.com>

Change-Id: Ibd624d9f95ee68b20a15891f639ddd5b3188cdf9

oh, yeah so the idea came from wanting to check in the LVM code that the volume group was based on a partition node, and not an actual device node, because i don't think that will work.  i was going to stack that on this"}, {'account_id': 6133, 'date': '2017-08-21 07:51:21.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

ok then still wip, right?'}, {'account_id': 21741, 'date': '2017-08-26 07:40:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

The reason sounds strange:
A block device is a block device - no matter of the type.

It is completely fine (and I need this ;-) ) to directly place LVMs in an image. It should be possible to place any block device into another - therefore there *should* be no test for the type here.'}]

commit_message:
Add node list to get_edges()

Pass the node list as a dictionary to a plugins get_edges() call.  The
initial idea is that we can use it to validate the 'base:' node is of
a type we expect; test case is shown to update this.

Change-Id: Iee3b341bcf88e897af611b7ae0d60fd07cb8da8d

I have a general worry that this kind of big change from pike will cause problems for projects that haven't yet created a pike branch.  They've opted into using constraints but they don't have the ability to gate with 'pike' constraints while they're stabilising for pike.

Also any instability in the gate as a whole would be bad at this stage of the release.

Smaller changes where we can assess the impact are fine especially if there is a human driving them.

I know that leaving these changes for too long has it's own pain but we can deal with that later."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2017-08-18 12:15:57.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 22: Verified-1

commit_message:
Add NIC Mapping Reporting Feature

The -i or --interfaces flag will print out a dict of the NIC
mappings if no interfaces are specified, or it will print a
list of the real interface names that match the interfaces
given. If a real interface name is given, it will be returned
in the list without translation only if it is live.

It has always been technically possible to map an interface
using an alias that matches an inactive real interface. This
change preserves that functionality, but will prevent mapping
using the name of an active interface. A warning will be
printed if an alias matches an inactive inteface.

Also change _is_active_nic and _mapped_nics to public functions
since they are called outside of utils.

Change-Id: I74af5391165e10f04800ea05e4204a7d1f74f526
Closes-bug: 1713137

[{'created': '2017-08-24 16:42:24.000000000', 'message': "Don't pass puppet-pacemaker.yaml to containerized HA envs

This shouldn't change functionality, as container_args would override
values from this env file when both containerized_overcloud and
enable_pacemaker are set to true. However, we wouldn't be recommending
users to deploy with both `-e puppet-pacemaker.yaml -e docker-ha.yaml`
at the same time, so we shouldn't be passing it like that in OOOQ
either.

The change is from a patch by Wes [1], instead of which we merged a
different patch in the end, but i believe we still need at least this
part from it.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/491146

Change-Id: I9e0858b5cee8d14e69f218cd9957079787b92db8
Co-Authored-By: Wesley Hayutin <weshayutin@gmail.com>

"}]
commit_message:
Don't pass puppet-pacemaker.yaml to containerized HA envs

This shouldn't change functionality, as container_args would override
values from this env file when both containerized_overcloud and
enable_pacemaker are set to true. However, we wouldn't be recommending
users to deploy with both `-e puppet-pacemaker.yaml -e docker-ha.yaml`
at the same time, so we shouldn't be passing it like that in OOOQ
either.

The change is from a patch by Wes [1], instead of which we merged a
different patch in the end, but i believe we still need at least this
part from it.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/491146

Change-Id: I9e0858b5cee8d14e69f218cd9957079787b92db8
Co-Authored-By: Wesley Hayutin <weshayutin@gmail.com>
Related-Bug: #1712070

commit_message:
Add stunnel

In order to configure tls for redis, we need to use stunnel to handle
the encryption.

Change-Id: If239144185ae398932ea897d6ad4d657a1044572
Related-Blueprint: tls-via-certmonger
(cherry picked from commit 07fe5ae7c7f8b3151e753e9b9682d071eccbd463)

commit_message:
doc migration: new directory layout

This patch introduces a new directory layout
in doc/source in conformance with the OpenStack
manuals project migration spec [1], moves the
existing content in manila/doc/source into the
new directories, and adjusts index files accordingly.

This is the first step in the migration process
as outlined in the spec.

[1] https://specs.openstack.org/openstack/docs-specs/specs/pike/os-manuals-migration.html

Partial-Bug: #1706181
Change-Id: I6b876f6e697659a5fe7046d5c5d4fd4ed98f9828
Needed-By: If13ebd1ede6fbc997d74425ec78e15621f1f80b2
Depends-On: I834fbef9783739fd664246ff710df1ab42ce2af5
Depends-On: Ia750cb049c0f53a234ea70ce1f2bbbb7a2aa9454

commit_message:
doc migration: openstackdocstheme completion

This patch completes the transition from oslosphinx

commit_message:
Add probe test for ssync of unexpired metadata to an expired object

Verify that metadata can be sync'd to a frag that has missed a POST
and consequently that frag appears to be expired, when in fact the
POST removed the X-Delete-At header.

Tests the fix added by the Related-Change.

Related-Bug: #1683689
Related-Change: I919994ead2b20dbb6c5671c208823e8b7f513715
Co-Authored-By: Clay Gerrard <clay.gerrard@gmail.com>

Change-Id: I9af9fc26098893db4043cc9a8d05d772772d4259

commit_message:
Fix no-change updates of failed resources with restricted actions

If a resource is in a FAILED state, but the plugin overrides
_needs_update() to not raise UpdateReplace, and also no actual update is
required, we simply change the resource's state to UPDATE_COMPLETE.
However, if there were restricted actions set in the environment, this code
path was not executed. The behaviour should be the same regardless of
whether there are restrictions that have been checked.

Change-Id: Ib3ed081f9f26f4f9172c681bf9ebccb7cdc3ca9c
Related-Bug: #1663522

commit_message:
Update versions of python clients from global requirments

Otherwise this causes sometimes issues like this:

 (python-cinderclient 2.2.0 (/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages),
  Requirement.parse('python-cinderclient>=3.0.0'),
  set(['python-openstackclient'])):

ContextualVersionConflict:
  (python-cinderclient 2.2.0 (/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages),
  Requirement.parse('python-cinderclient>=3.0.0'), set(['python-openstackclient']))

commit_message:
VMware: use WithRetrieval in ds_util module

This change uses WithRetrieval[1] in nova.virt.vmwareapi.ds_util to
delegate VMware pagination to WithRetrieval.

[1] oslo.vmware.vim_util

Change-Id: Ifb29bd0dcc2133a45698310133e97e51d6d275e1

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-08-25 22:18:06.000000000', 'message': "Fix DirectClientExceptions with utf-8 encoded paths

Because the direct_client module uses the buffered_http module it's
requests are already robust to receiving either unicode or utf-8 paths.

The DirectClientException message however encodes the given path with
the device key from a ring node - which having come from a json
de-serialized ring will be a unicode type.  Despite the device key
almost always being only ascii characters; python string interpolation
with any unicode type will always force all binary strings to be
converted to unicode - which will raise an error if any byte strings
includes non-ascii characters.

To maintain robustness in DirectClientException, when the provided path
is not already unicode we decode the bytes as utf-8 before mixing them
with the other unicode strings and then normalize everything back to a
quoted utf-8 byte string.

Change-Id: I162d2e093a3110856d6e1d513de3c7919079c9e7
"}]
commit_message:
Fix DirectClientExceptions with utf-8 encoded paths

Because the direct_client module uses the buffered_http module it's
requests are already robust to receiving either unicode or utf-8 paths.

The DirectClientException message however encodes the given path with
the device key from a ring node - which having come from a json
de-serialized ring will be a unicode type.  Despite the device key
almost always being only ascii characters; python string interpolation
with any unicode type will always force all binary strings to be
converted to unicode - which will raise an error if any byte strings
includes non-ascii characters.

To maintain robustness in DirectClientException, when the provided path
is not already unicode we decode the bytes as utf-8 before mixing them
with the other unicode strings and then normalize everything back to a
quoted utf-8 byte string.

Change-Id: I162d2e093a3110856d6e1d513de3c7919079c9e7

commit_message:
Fix DefaultSubnetPool API test

As default subnetpool is a unique resource in the cloud, it needs to be
cleaned after each test is done. This patch adds a cleanup call to
DefaultSubnetPool tests in order to delete created default subnet pool.

Change-Id: I4c963d0d0e9910f7047061b51feb36c8a19de65c
Closes-bug: #1709938
(cherry picked from commit 637734c1b6d5a158374576ce27941a04363fc8bb)

commit_message:
Fix test_keepalived_ipv6_support for Keepalived v1.2.20

In commit [1] (some explanation in [2] ) VRRP initialisation is enhanced
to read source IP address(to use when sending VRRP packets) from the
HA interface or from keepalived config("unicast_src_ip" parameter).
If it is unable to find IP address, VRRP initialisation will fail with
error "Cannot find an IP address to use for interface".

In the test, we set vrrp->family to AF_INET by setting vip to
169.254.0.1/24 through config, but not providing source IPv4 address(i.e
no 'unicast_src_ip' option or no IP on HA interface), making the test
to fail with [1]. To fix that, we set the IP address on HA interface.

Note: Commit [1] is added in Keepalived version 1.2.20.
Tested the fix on both Keepalived v1.2.19 and Keepalived v1.2.20.

[1] https://github.com/acassen/keepalived/commit/37488e57
[2] https://github.com/acassen/keepalived/issues/445

Closes-bug: #1712388
Change-Id: I260c0e6810ed54c93f93621afa6ab13855ef2428
(cherry picked from commit 334a1ed7d52afa21230db8588dd4cc1673386ae3)

commit_message:
Fix test_keepalived_ipv6_support for Keepalived v1.2.20

In commit [1] (some explanation in [2] ) VRRP initialisation is enhanced
to read source IP address(to use when sending VRRP packets) from the
HA interface or from keepalived config("unicast_src_ip" parameter).
If it is unable to find IP address, VRRP initialisation will fail with
error "Cannot find an IP address to use for interface".

In the test, we set vrrp->family to AF_INET by setting vip to
169.254.0.1/24 through config, but not providing source IPv4 address(i.e
no 'unicast_src_ip' option or no IP on HA interface), making the test
to fail with [1]. To fix that, we set the IP address on HA interface.

Note: Commit [1] is added in Keepalived version 1.2.20.
Tested the fix on both Keepalived v1.2.19 and Keepalived v1.2.20.

[1] https://github.com/acassen/keepalived/commit/37488e57
[2] https://github.com/acassen/keepalived/issues/445

Closes-bug: #1712388
Change-Id: I260c0e6810ed54c93f93621afa6ab13855ef2428
(cherry picked from commit 334a1ed7d52afa21230db8588dd4cc1673386ae3)

commit_message:
Return neutron-ns-metadata-proxy threads to 1000

A wsgi threads change [1] also changed the number of threads the
neutron-ns-metadata-proxy process has down to 100.  At some sites this
low setting is leading to failures.
This patch increases only the neutron-ns-metadata-proxy default thread count
back up to 1000 to resolve these failures.

This is not a cherry pick from Ocata as this code was removed in Ocata
in favor of using HAProxy with a setting of 1024 [2].

[1] https://review.openstack.org/278007/
[2] https://review.openstack.org/431691

Change-Id: I59cb05e165c6daa4ce0a1b636450f66fb699e88e
Closes-Bug: #1711215

commit_message:
rehome qos api definition

This patch rehomes neutron's qos extension's API definition into
neutron-lib. UTs and a release note are also included.

Reviewers:
Please note the difference in the SUB_RESOURCE_ATTRIBUTE_MAP attributes
herein vs those in the original. Here we've added conversion to int on
a few attributes and also removed the default value of None for those.

Change-Id: I8ab3712850ec02278b3efb9161fc03236926b842

[{'created': '2017-08-25 18:20:08.000000000', 'message': "Remove cluster-change-departed hook

The cluster-change-departed hook is tied to the cluster-changed
hook. In the cluster changed hook, there is logic to ensure the
initial admin exists which makes calls to the keystone service.
If the remote database has already been removed (as seen in recent
CI runs), then this will cause the hook to fail execution.

This is safe to remove as the primary purpose of the cluster-changed
hook is to sync the SSL keys and update identity relation units.
There should be no need to sync the keys when a unit is departing
the cluster relation. Likewise, the update of the identity relations
are not needed either as the VIP is used for access to the keystone
services by remote units and the access credentials won't change.

Change-Id: Id8fed284557f67f5676189ec8951b778cf506c97
Closes-Bug: #1713108
"}]
commit_message:
Remove cluster-change-departed hook

The cluster-change-departed hook is tied to the cluster-changed
hook. In the cluster changed hook, there is logic to ensure the
initial admin exists which makes calls to the keystone service.
If the remote database has already been removed (as seen in recent
CI runs), then this will cause the hook to fail execution.

This is safe to remove as the primary purpose of the cluster-changed
hook is to sync the SSL keys and update identity relation units.
There should be no need to sync the keys when a unit is departing
the cluster relation. Likewise, the update of the identity relations
are not needed either as the VIP is used for access to the keystone
services by remote units and the access credentials won't change.

Change-Id: Id8fed284557f67f5676189ec8951b778cf506c97
Closes-Bug: #1713108

commit_message:
Prefix tasks with ostack versions

The DB migrations are using recurring task names,
making it difficult to isolate which version task ran.
The prefix of each task with the actual base OpenStack
version makes it easier to identify those, especially
in a leapfrog situation.

Change-Id: I9c2b711452208be28bef421a5e536bd2bf8a9a03

commit_message:
Enable ceilometer compute agent

This service isn't being started by default and it's required in order
to ceilometer collect data about cpu, which is required to run tempest
integration tests

Closes-Bug: #1713038
Change-Id: I79ba7744db78636fba78e041443148c91e06f940

commit_message:
Add panko publisher in the event pipeline

Even though panko is deprecated, we still enable it by default.
So lets keep it in pipeline as well until its fully dead.

Change-Id: Idac89820a66c59b921551857cccae6dbc38241c3

commit_message:
Move multinode overcloud user to multinode settings

Move overcloud-ssh-user settings from env settings in extra args
to multinode settings in deploy role. It's relevant to all
multinode jobs we have.

Change-Id: Ia409617cab5a31f19875844c676dad87518977fc

like "ko-KR". This is fixed now for the upcoming Babel 2.4.1 release.

To be able to publish translated content, blacklist Babel 2.4.0.

For details, see
https://github.com/python-babel/babel/issues/489

Change-Id: I3bd63b3c4798270890c7cabe1d4e7aedf1aaa1ed

'}]
commit_message:
Blacklist Babel 2.4.0

Babel 2.4.0 does not handle "-" in locale po files
like "ko-KR". This is fixed now for the upcoming Babel 2.4.1 release.

To be able to publish translated content, blacklist Babel 2.4.0.

For details, see
https://github.com/python-babel/babel/issues/489

Change-Id: I3bd63b3c4798270890c7cabe1d4e7aedf1aaa1ed
(cherry picked from commit a6f7497e597f9395a4b139d629213f21fe8074d7)

and as such it can't simply use pip's cryptography wheel/binary,
which by default is linked to libssl.so.10.

"}]
commit_message:
Add OpenSuse SAIO build instructions

This patch adds OpenSuse to the build a SAIO development page.

OpenSuse's libssl.so naming is different then other Linux distros
and as such it can't simply use pip's cryptography wheel/binary,
which by default is linked to libssl.so.10.
To fix this, --no-binary cryptography was added to pip install:

  pip install --no-binary cryptography -r requirements.txt

Which forces the cryptography module's binding to be compiled
against the correct libssl.so library.

Change-Id: I6a070f33d670edbb887433530c44e2cb509f0c58

commit_message:
Export ANSIBLE_CONFIG so we can make sure it's used by Ansible

Ansible will read the configuration file found at ANSIBLE_CONFIG
automatically, regardless of location.
This ensures that scripts that run in the same context as
devstack-vm-gate-wrap.sh inherit from the same Ansible configuration.

This fixes the fact that network overlay playbook runs were missing
from the ARA report as they were running from "devstack-vm-gate.sh".

Change-Id: I53c30bc72477671f38b04f0331862e2bbfaed4d2

commit_message:
Tempest: Fix cleaning of networks after API tests

In case when network was created with different than default
client (like admin_client) network wasn't properly removed in
cleanup_resources method because default client was used to
delete function and 'NotFound' error returned from Neutron
was silently ignored in such case.

Now networks created by different than default client are
added to "admin_networks" list and are cleaned by admin_client.

Change-Id: I52428262276c16dbe077fcf77b1890f12dccc97d
(cherry picked from commit 35b3e7b3cf24f88ea58a8743225f7ba61e77f356)

commit_message:
Tempest: Fix cleaning of networks after API tests

In case when network was created with different than default
client (like admin_client) network wasn't properly removed in
cleanup_resources method because default client was used to
delete function and 'NotFound' error returned from Neutron
was silently ignored in such case.

Now networks created by different than default client are
added to "admin_networks" list and are cleaned by admin_client.

Change-Id: I52428262276c16dbe077fcf77b1890f12dccc97d
(cherry picked from commit 35b3e7b3cf24f88ea58a8743225f7ba61e77f356)

commit_message:
Nova: Support Cinder Volume Attachement using Ceph Backend

This PS enables cinder volume attachment for nova when used with ceph.

Change-Id: I9772f38fb3a1a9af26bd92ee18a651d3372de64c

commit_message:
accept the first match as the result

Rather than reporting multiple matches, stop evaluating rules when we
get the first match. This will still report redirect failures, and
avoids a false-negative when a more specific rule appears before a
more general rule and the more specific rule is valid.

Change-Id: Ie909301a367659a0ce199000342bcdc9422ce801
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

commit_message:
Move old validators to the new style

* Move valid_command validator under the new plugin base and put it
  under VMTask module, since it is hardcoded for only one type of
  scenarios
* Move flavor_exists to openstack plugins
* Move workbook_contains_workflow to openstack plugins and rename
  'workbook' argument to unified 'param_name'
* Deprecate validate_share_proto in favor of enum validator
* Deprecate an old mechanism for validators

Co-Authored-By: Andrey Kurilin <andr.kurilin@gmail.com>

Change-Id: Ic7b5687d5d83b7f032dd61a9ccc99c6236d63157

commit_message:
Fix message for required_params validator

`required_params` validator support the case OR which means that at
least one argument from thelist should be specified. In this case only
the last argument from the list was included in the error message.

This patch fixes an error message in this case. Also, it replaces the
outdated word benchmark by task.

Change-Id: I89dade2f045ad260e70268684fb3f1656fb051d0

commit_message:
Add back in keystone v3 support for basic_deployment.py

A recent commit (ecfd7a64ad57235714e582edfc788473463160a6) tidied up the
keystone authentication in basic_deployment.py across most of the
charms. Barbican was a bit different in that it has an explicit v3 test
as it was implemented a bit odly and so needed a v3 test for the main
barbican software.

This fix puts back in keystone v3 support for basic_deployment.py

Change-Id: Ic689914402b7966632530d5d595d64f87f3e95bf
Closes-Bug: #1712849

Remove another outdated note

We don't support releases older than newton anymore, so there's no
need for a note that documents changes in that release.

commit_message:
Use API level filtering for nova_security_group provider

In order to speed things up and avoid pulling all the groups,
we can instead provide it to the client and it will filter
things at the API level speeding the process up.

Change-Id: I6798218a3695bfced781056b12a192b82733eea6
(cherry picked from commit 414ae8da0ae637ce5059207d7834241f6421ed54)

commit_message:
Increase minimum puppetlabs-stdlib version requirement

ensure_resources which is used in the 'horizon' class
only came in at 4.12.0 so increase version to that.

Change-Id: I06875ebc95c556a091837c642529d4f9ce9e103d

commit_message:
Make horizon_ca optional when SSL is enabled

This allows the vhost to use the globally set CA file (in ssl.conf) if
present. Or one might just not need the CA to be set (no TLS
authentication).

Change-Id: Iba1aea34e72a0138120fa7bcb7267f73e37bf0ce
Closes-Bug: #1711280

commit_message:
Update Install Docs for Pike on SUSE

Update to repositories for Pike on SUSE.
Update distribution versions for SLES and openSUSE.
Update links in appendix to go to pike resources.

remove some extra whitespace and use #. for lists.

Change-Id: I5b7e3b45850a3b9a24ba81a16acda9ade4ab5255

commit_message:
Add opendaylight role to tests a-r-r

In order to pass the lint test, all meta-dep
roles for the roles we execute in the test must
be present. As the os_neutron role recently got
the opendaylight role added as a meta-dep it is
now required here too.

Change-Id: I0069d97528382e0ce234a8e83ad4ed5ab52dc56c

signing-artifacts, we actually get a copy from the private key.

'}]
commit_message:
Remove public gpg_key

Right now, no jobs actually need the public keym, so remove it. For
signing-artifacts, we actually get a copy from the private key.

Change-Id: I61e147b7df2b07fe83c460fdfd1fb6bcea2e245f
Signed-off-by: Paul Belanger <pabelanger@redhat.com>

commit_message:
DNAT: use cached floating lport

Before all ports were cached, floating lport had to be retrieved from
the NB database. Since we cache the ports, we don't have to retrieve
them any longer.

This code will take any code blocks for 'bash' or 'console' and output
them to the doc/build/code_sample directory. Such files could then be

commit_message:
Refactor IP configuration loading

Previously the set_used_ips function did all of the work to read the
configuration and inventory data to determine how to mark IPs as used.

This changeset splits that work into separate functions, one for
configuration and inventory, and uses their output to the set the used
IPs.

The information was separated this way in preparation for using with an
IPManager instance instead of the Queue.Queue and set objects in the
future.

Also added were tests for the configuration and inventory parsing. The
TestSetUsedIPS test was moved into the test_ips module for
consistency. In addition, the test was slightly changed to properly
exercise the iteration over the dictionary of bridges-to-IPs.

Change-Id: Idb518f7e6aff1b60f1b9cdf567f42e422c7ead4b

commit_message:
[POC] [WIP] Populate group vars from env/config

This patchset is a proof of concept seeking to answer the following:

Given a valid config/environment, can a group_vars directory be produced
such that an AIO could be built using Ansible's group_vars mechanism
instead of OSA's current one?

This will be tested with the AIO env/configuration used in the gate. The
process is likely to be creating a script that will parse the existing
configuration, outputting those values into a directory hierarchy, then
popluating the files with the current config values.

Change-Id: I4735fd5dbb5a1c9bc48657d6a443ecc8f7262e0d

commit_message:
Separate host type and container type with a dash

In order to support DNS-enabled container names, underscores must be
replaced with dashes. This commmit begins that transition by replacing
one of the container name templates.

A test is provided to confirm that new hosts can be added to an existing
inventory with the previous format.

Change-Id: I40b4f9ec391cd51d3f77837489d48d26951cb0f8
Partial-Bug: #1643680

commit_message:
Install swift serially for rolling updates

In order to reduce downtime, update swift nodes once at a time during
install/upgrade. This keeps the API and data available without
interruption.

The storage nodes are updated first, so that the proxy nodes can route
around the downtime for a single server. Then the proxy nodes are
updated one at a time.

Depends-On: Ice3b4526609f5a5fd4472c8408de9ed08aea29e6
Depends-On: I837e31e5f17b31d4cd6191df196acd3c91bfc91e
Change-Id: Ia6117764beccd88a03456de0b0c1faa66f833d68

commit_message:
Add test for Horizon group membership

This commit currently seeks to test behavior when a host group name and a
container group name collide. The fix is not currently known, but tests
are being provided to at least isolate the behavior.

Addresses-Bug: #1623584

Change-Id: I4f0a376f202ed68ff6ccefd795c455328283b8df

commit_message:
VMware:Use power_state const for power state check

VMware Nova driver does not support hot-plugging and
hot-unplugging of IDE drives. It checks the instance
power state using the power state string returned by
vSphere API after converting it to lower case. Commit
c9653a3b83a5d00bb52c01c868797f458f9d0174 replaced power
state strings with constants from power_state module,
but missed the validation code in attaching/detaching
IDE drives. Fixing this validation by replacing the
power state strings with corresponding constants in
power_state module.

Co-Authored-By: Sihan Wang <wsihan@vmware.com>
Change-Id: I0aad8457d55a6b1d190e8629e02f5e0033a9dcfe
Closes-bug: #1680254

commit_message:
Update bindep for python-apt/pyOpenSSL

This patch updates the newton bindep.txt to include the
python2-pyOpenSSL to pyOpenSSL switch. Also, it adds the
python-apt packages that are required for running ansible
playbooks in test mode.

Change-Id: I3449e278465f46b4e853ad06ec9eb9446dd5522f

commit_message:
snmp: Fix discovery when total memory is missing

In 7348c156a8032c09e2046aa23d95fcf996b39db3, we fix some case
where the oid value was not existed.

The post operation for "memory_avail" does not use the generic function
for getting oid value and is impacted by already fixed bug.

This change uses get_oid_value for "memory_avail" like any other place
to fix the issue.

Change-Id: I4b944716af301534a0906dd0ea6117c18c913d50
Closes-bug: #1707859
(cherry picked from commit 61fec88d4e7798d9301f36495ed4c1d54515a43b)

commit_message:
Fixes import_modules_recursively for Windows

The neutron agents fail to start on Windows, due to the fact that
neutron.common.utils.import_modules_recursively expects the paths
to be forwardslash separated, while on Windows they are backslash
separated.

Change-Id: I5e15273c2f70b70fad0cf1216ef0b33c6a99d702
Closes-Bug: #1694220

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-08-23 13:23:57.000000000', 'message': "Delete controller for standalone OVS bridges

The patch adds an OVS extra parameter to delete controller for bridges
configured with standalone fail mode. By default, bridges are created
without having an openflow controllers. If node is restarted, the bridge
is set to standalone mode but if a service managing the bridge sets a
controller, it will remain in the ovsdb.

As ovs-vswitchd sets the bridge behavior to normal MAC learning switch
only if bridge in standalone mode can't communicate with its controller,
leaving controller defined can cause node outage when bridge is used as
management network. In such case controller service, like
neutron-openvswitch-agent, would need to communicate over management
network but given that bridge is in standalone mode but communicates
with controller, management network won't be reachable. This creates a
chicken-egg problem.

By removing controller by default, ovs-vswitchd implements a normal
action rule to the standalone bridge and service can use the bridge as
management network and eventually set the brdige to secure and set the
flows manually.

See opened Bugzilla for more information:
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1473763

Change-Id: Iad48312667834ea8f5c7145595ae89cb5159b36d
(cherry picked from commit f8d76d2cdebfa0d06233a59a8f6539207c5b5a4e)
"}, {'created': '2017-08-23 13:46:32.000000000', 'message': "Delete controller for standalone OVS bridges

The patch adds an OVS extra parameter to delete controller for bridges
configured with standalone fail mode. By default, bridges are created
without having an openflow controllers. If node is restarted, the bridge
is set to standalone mode but if a service managing the bridge sets a
controller, it will remain in the ovsdb.

As ovs-vswitchd sets the bridge behavior to normal MAC learning switch
only if bridge in standalone mode can't communicate with its controller,
leaving controller defined can cause node outage when bridge is used as
management network. In such case controller service, like
neutron-openvswitch-agent, would need to communicate over management
network but given that bridge is in standalone mode but communicates
with controller, management network won't be reachable. This creates a
chicken-egg problem.

By removing controller by default, ovs-vswitchd implements a normal
action rule to the standalone bridge and service can use the bridge as
management network and eventually set the brdige to secure and set the
flows manually.

See opened Bugzilla for more information:
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1473763

Closes-bug: #1712517

Change-Id: Iad48312667834ea8f5c7145595ae89cb5159b36d
(cherry picked from commit f8d76d2cdebfa0d06233a59a8f6539207c5b5a4e)

commit_message:
Delete controller for standalone OVS bridges

The patch adds an OVS extra parameter to delete controller for bridges
configured with standalone fail mode. By default, bridges are created
without having an openflow controllers. If node is restarted, the bridge
is set to standalone mode but if a service managing the bridge sets a
controller, it will remain in the ovsdb.

As ovs-vswitchd sets the bridge behavior to normal MAC learning switch
only if bridge in standalone mode can't communicate with its controller,
leaving controller defined can cause node outage when bridge is used as
management network. In such case controller service, like
neutron-openvswitch-agent, would need to communicate over management
network but given that bridge is in standalone mode but communicates
with controller, management network won't be reachable. This creates a
chicken-egg problem.

By removing controller by default, ovs-vswitchd implements a normal
action rule to the standalone bridge and service can use the bridge as
management network and eventually set the brdige to secure and set the
flows manually.

See opened Bugzilla for more information:
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1473763

Closes-bug: #1712517

Change-Id: Iad48312667834ea8f5c7145595ae89cb5159b36d
(cherry picked from commit f8d76d2cdebfa0d06233a59a8f6539207c5b5a4e)

commit_message:
Add /bin to PATH for CRL cronjob

Checking the root's mail (/var/mail/root) I finally saw the root cause
of the CRL cronjob not working.

/bin/sh: curl: command not found

now, curl, (and most commands used by that cronjob) is in the /bin bash,
so we need to add it to the environment's PATH for the cronjob.

Change-Id: If10855b801782eeaf2006cd57071d74d13daf8c2
Closes-Bug: #1712404
(cherry picked from commit 139ac85028947f476a085e89bd54f3dfacd886cf)

commit_message:
Stop logging versions on every agent update

This logging statement was being called on every agent update
even if no versions changed, resulting in a bunch of useless
messages.

We already log when the actual versions change in the _set_version
call here: [1]

To cover the cases where versions are removed, this adds two logging
statements so we can be sure we see when the tracked versions do
change but not be bothered by version logs in any other condition.

1.
http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/neutron/tree/neutron/api/rpc/callbacks/version_manager.py?h=d225b86738a9db56bc643dfe637b1f21393ad27e#n113

Partial-Bug: #1707307
Change-Id: I4761d21257dabfbd661bba1b24fe09d208d16ae6

In case when network was created with different than default
client (like admin_client) network wasn't properly removed in
cleanup_resources method because default client was used to
delete function and 'NotFound' error returned from Neutron
was silently ignored in such case.

'}]
commit_message:
Tempest: Fix cleaning of networks after API tests

In case when network was created with different than default
client (like admin_client) network wasn't properly removed in
cleanup_resources method because default client was used to
delete function and 'NotFound' error returned from Neutron
was silently ignored in such case.

Now networks created by different than default client are
added to "admin_networks" list and are cleaned by admin_client.

Change-Id: I52428262276c16dbe077fcf77b1890f12dccc97d

commit_message:
Allow Agent object to be queryable by dict's key field

This Patchset allows Agent to do query like this:
agent.Agent.get_objects_by_dict_field_key(
            'resource_versions', 'obj1', self.context)[0]
And this is needed by lots of Agent's unittests

Change-Id: I3af7fb9349f12ea94484a875e58ea35c76b33af2

[{'created': '2017-08-25 14:49:02.000000000', 'message': 'Split log permission changes from rsync command

Unfortunately the version of rsync used by CentOS

The rsync command is adjusted to ignore ownership

commit_message:
Split log permission changes from rsync command

Unfortunately the version of rsync used by CentOS
(3.0.x) does not support the use of the --chown
option, so we need to go back to doing it in a
separate command.

The rsync command is adjusted to ignore ownership
and permissions when copying, reverting to the
target folder defaults. Then in the log folder
we make sure it has permissions for the jenkins
user. The chmod is done first to ensure that all
dirs are traversable.

Some line breaks are added to the script to help
make it a little more readable.

Change-Id: I74157f7bc449ff7ee6d2e280dff54b2c9ebfa9f0
(cherry picked from commit 56a6dabdcada7f0635a17d6765802c1f8bc7b087)

commit_message:
Call methods with kwargs instead of positionals

If a method is defined with kwargs it should be called with
kwargs. Calling a method that has specified kwargs with positional
arguments is fragile and should be avoided. It leaves the caller
open to breakages if the method signature of the callee ever changes.
If the callee's signature changes, it requires the callers to be
updated, even if they aren't using the new functionality or if the
argument doesn't apply to them.

This change applies that practice to parts of the assignment API.
This will make it easier to reuse the existing assignment driver to
implement global role assignments.

bp global-roles

Change-Id: I0a228ec25cd88f456cacd5824082f1b322e0262d

commit_message:
Switch etcd base driver to use etcd3gw

python-etcd does not support V3 of etcd's API.
Switching to an updated library with the etcd3 API
will allow us to implement a Pub/Sub mechanism
using the 'watch' option.

Change-Id: I4b88b3f259a25509fb452d13d0a71bf1bd441abf

commit_message:
Allow v3.0 volume metadata API calls

Commit I575635258c10f299181b8e4cdb51a7ad1f1be764 added some optimization
to a few of the volume metadata API calls. It added a check incorrectly
for the microversion for those changes such that if you were not using
microversion 3.15 or above, it would fail the API call.

This changes the microversion check to correctly either perform the
new requested functionality or fail back to the base 3.0/2.0 API
behavior.

Change-Id: I09ad8200f73273dae8e5d926939620b71d9210e8
Closes-bug: #1712192
(cherry picked from commit c9c668437efb9e7f05a399472875b29c70f79d76)

[{'created': '2017-08-25 12:29:57.000000000', 'message': 'scripts: scripts-library.sh: Fix location for log directory

The AIO job did not collect any logs from the host because the working
directory was changing due to pushd commands and the logs were placed
into the wrong location. We already have the root location in the
OSA_CLONE_DIR variable so lets use that and only try to detect it if
that variable is empty for whatever reason.

Change-Id: I17cc321ab640da4e251d21a996b537bda8cb3c1d
(cherry picked from commit 836703a0c34fd100e5402b2cd50c3647ca73f4e1)
'}]
commit_message:
scripts: scripts-library.sh: Fix location for log directory

The AIO job did not collect any logs from the host because the working
directory was changing due to pushd commands and the logs were placed
into the wrong location. We already have the root location in the
OSA_CLONE_DIR variable so lets use that and only try to detect it if
that variable is empty for whatever reason.

Change-Id: I17cc321ab640da4e251d21a996b537bda8cb3c1d
(cherry picked from commit 836703a0c34fd100e5402b2cd50c3647ca73f4e1)

commit_message:
Install specific puppet-openstack_spec_helper release for testing

When running beaker tests, puppet-openstack_spec_helper is installed
using the Gemfile which means that it will download the master even
if we are testing puppet-openstack_spec_helper itself in the gate.

This patch will make sure that we have the right version which
is being tested.

Change-Id: I8b3d86f63c86e8ce30ff180aa2c5845d4fe77672

commit_message:
[DNM] [RFC] [Nova] Fix for volume-attach when using cinder & ceph

    For comment only as it's entirely compatible with the ceph-secrets
    merge and need further work.

--

A few small fixes as well as revert/dumb-down earlier logic for ceph
user/configuration which looks to have only been partially merged so
that we now have functional volume-attach.

Change-Id: I6696d7c52163b4b7cd593dd10208765ac172d1f9

commit_message:
Fix import of osa_toolkit in inventory-manage.py

Add the location of the osa_tookit directory to Python's library paths
to allow its modules to be imported.

Closes-Bug: 1711223
Change-Id: I70b0ce6e6415499617c0c83b1232813df07772cf
(cherry picked from commit 18464e47f156d6947c21b9b27069d886feefd799)

commit_message:
Bump SHAs for Pike final rc

Moving towards final RC for pike, we should aim to keep the SHAs for
upstream projects, and OSA roles updated. This patch bumps SHAs to keep
these updated as of 25/08/2017.

Change-Id: Ia34aa4c904701cb6ba07eca16b604cbf2a7e1191

commit_message:
Enable keystonemiddleware cache encryption

This patch set enables keystonemiddleware memcache encryption by providing a
random string key into the service configuration file, and setting the
memcache_security_strategy as ENCRYPT.

Change-Id: Ia030f5414308a29096c644bae70047a323eaffde

commit_message:
tripleo-quickstart: run tripleo upgrade jobs in check

The Ansible roles for TripleO upgrades in CI are in Quickstart, so we
need to test the jobs everytime we patch quickstart.

Change-Id: Icfbe13122161f21c8a97f312050096664281f118

[{'created': '2017-08-25 09:34:16.000000000', 'message': 'vars: suse: Add ca-certificates-mozilla package in LXC image

Ever since we stopped installing recommended packages in the LXC images
(I4d373346cf85ca037f1520058f6a3bce18489e3c) things started to fall
apart because we are missing the certificates provided in the
ca-certificates-mozilla package. As such, add it to the list of
recommended packages. This fixes the following error which only
occurs inside a container:

2017-08-24 11:06:47.346515 | fatal: [infra1]: FAILED! => {"attempts": 5,"changed": false, "failed": true, "msg": "Failed to validate the SSL
certificate for bootstrap.pypa.io:443. Make sure your managed systems have a valid CA certificate installed. You can use validate_certs=False
if you do not need to confirm the servers identity but this is unsafe and not recommended. Paths checked for this platform: /etc/ssl/certs,
/etc/pki/ca-trust/extracted/pem, /etc/pki/tls/certs, /usr/share/ca-certificates/cacert.org, /etc/ansible. The exception msg
was: [SSL: CERTIFICATE_VERIFY_FAILED] certificate verify failed (_ssl.c:661)."}

Change-Id: I857ffc350b5164630589c286b661304606e12f95
(cherry picked from commit 06c6f37eb9e978a98a381dde8cb8f34202263a59)
'}]
commit_message:
vars: suse: Add ca-certificates-mozilla package in LXC image

Ever since we stopped installing recommended packages in the LXC images
(I4d373346cf85ca037f1520058f6a3bce18489e3c) things started to fall
apart because we are missing the certificates provided in the
ca-certificates-mozilla package. As such, add it to the list of
recommended packages. This fixes the following error which only
occurs inside a container:

2017-08-24 11:06:47.346515 | fatal: [infra1]: FAILED! => {"attempts": 5,"changed": false, "failed": true, "msg": "Failed to validate the SSL
certificate for bootstrap.pypa.io:443. Make sure your managed systems have a valid CA certificate installed. You can use validate_certs=False
if you do not need to confirm the servers identity but this is unsafe and not recommended. Paths checked for this platform: /etc/ssl/certs,
/etc/pki/ca-trust/extracted/pem, /etc/pki/tls/certs, /usr/share/ca-certificates/cacert.org, /etc/ansible. The exception msg
was: [SSL: CERTIFICATE_VERIFY_FAILED] certificate verify failed (_ssl.c:661)."}

Change-Id: I857ffc350b5164630589c286b661304606e12f95
(cherry picked from commit 06c6f37eb9e978a98a381dde8cb8f34202263a59)

[{'created': '2017-08-24 10:33:09.000000000', 'message': 'Fix for appending custom volumes

Before this change, there was no ability to append custom volume for
any of the services. The reason was a missing new line character, so
the templates were formatted like this:
- name: pod-shared
  mountPath: /tmp/pod-shared - mountPath: /tmp/test2
  name: test2

Apart from that, for some of the services (mostly job-bootstrap) invalid
indentation for custom volumes (and their mounts) was set.

Closes-Bug: 1712745
Change-Id: Ib57c76a34c0e28ad9e67ea47d1fc250b17711a42
Signed-off-by: Mateusz Blaszkowski <mateusz.blaszkowski@intel.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Fix for appending custom volumes

Before this change, there was no ability to append custom volume for
any of the services. The reason was a missing new line character, so
the templates were formatted like this:
- name: pod-shared
  mountPath: /tmp/pod-shared - mountPath: /tmp/test2
  name: test2

Apart from that, for some of the services (mostly job-bootstrap) invalid
indentation for custom volumes (and their mounts) was set.

Closes-Bug: 1712745
Change-Id: Ib57c76a34c0e28ad9e67ea47d1fc250b17711a42
Signed-off-by: Mateusz Blaszkowski <mateusz.blaszkowski@intel.com>

commit_message:
Add support for consecutive_build_service_disable_threshold

consecutive_build_service_disable_threshold was added to nova as part of
the Pike cycle. This setting can be used to allow the compute nodes to
disable themselves in the case of consecutive build failures.

Change-Id: If46602fdcac38745e6b6b17d560844bb4f42ba3c
Related-Bug: #1712632

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-08-24 17:34:02.000000000', 'message': 'Fix no_proxy evaluation for Swarm clusters

At the moment, no_proxy variable is evaluated separately for docker
daemon and for swarm-manager container running in docker. Evaluated
value for swarm-manager is not getting into cloud-init script, because
$NODE_PROXY token is getting replaced by Heat str_replace function.
This commit is intended to unify NO_PROXY evaluation and also fix the
issue with swarm-manager.

Related-Bug: #1647815
Related-Bug: #1632698
Related-Bug: #1660562
Change-Id: I336024265008b6cae308bf7b614476b71b81fa01
(cherry picked from commit 35dc923d66213edebf7db122dd929d79a8eb4cf7)
'}]
commit_message:
Fix no_proxy evaluation for Swarm clusters

At the moment, no_proxy variable is evaluated separately for docker
daemon and for swarm-manager container running in docker. Evaluated
value for swarm-manager is not getting into cloud-init script, because
$NODE_PROXY token is getting replaced by Heat str_replace function.
This commit is intended to unify NO_PROXY evaluation and also fix the
issue with swarm-manager.

Related-Bug: #1647815
Related-Bug: #1632698
Related-Bug: #1660562
Change-Id: I336024265008b6cae308bf7b614476b71b81fa01
(cherry picked from commit 35dc923d66213edebf7db122dd929d79a8eb4cf7)

commit_message:
Reduce package list on CentOS

This patch removes the Development Tools package group and adds in
gcc/git packages specifically. It should speed up the deployment.

Change-Id: I0695b8afc22476a7645345a9cd8f5b683bf347fd
(cherry picked from commit 94d01b51320780aa31e75acd7fed3b995cd3e194)

commit_message:
Fix the default port value

In the file cinder/volume/drivers/disco/disco.py, the default value
for disco_client_port and disco_src_api_port should be Integer.

Change-Id: I101560168670ad68bc807fed7d59552ffd332a2c

commit_message:
Split log permission changes from rsync command

Unfortunately the version of rsync used by CentOS
(3.0.x) does not support the use of the --chown
option, so we need to go back to doing it in a
separate command.

The rsync command is adjusted to ignore ownership
and permissions when copying, reverting to the
target folder defaults. Then in the log folder
we make sure it has permissions for the jenkins
user. The chmod is done first to ensure that all
dirs are traversable.

Some line breaks are added to the script to help
make it a little more readable.

Change-Id: I74157f7bc449ff7ee6d2e280dff54b2c9ebfa9f0

commit_message:
Exclude /etc directories properly

This patch fixes a bug where some directories in /etc were not being
excluded properly. It wasn't working because directories like
'/etc/selinux' weren't under /proc/$PID/root/etc and rsync wouldn't
exclude them.

Change-Id: I3aab89a7cc86964daae436594f60131e3b7549b3
(cherry picked from commit 617f3f0c33df78a3f5e4ce96f78168dc2091b149)

commit_message:
[Doc Bld Fix] Add links to man page contents

The pages under man/ had not been linked to from anywhere.  This
was causing Sphinx to issue warnings during build.  This patch
corrects that.

There was also a 'todo' directive that wasn't valid that needed
to be removed.  This patch also corrects that.

Change-Id: I8ab75b7be921a05e9e4eb023c4dfe90cf4404e6c
(cherry picked from commit be10de4b91c46825cb0e0d895e1ec6304ba6562a)

commit_message:
Support SUM based firmware update as clean step for iLO drivers

This commit adds support to perform Smart Update Manager (SUM)
based firmware update as an inband manual clean step
`update_firmware_sum` for iLO drivers.

Closes-Bug: #1648448
Change-Id: I581d5bc535420d4493394d16cf6cc2bb0ddeb8f7
(cherry picked from commit e3b8f518fa0fdc912df68e2e4d55a1e3c3fc4d74)

commit_message:
Ceph: update namespace client key script to hard fail sucessfully

This PS updates the ceph namespace client key script to hard fail
if it cannot get the admin storage key from the namespace ceph is
deployed into.

Change-Id: Ieefe6d800a678d721294561b25bbebc874cfa74d

commit_message:
Remove API races from backup

There is a potential window of opportunity where races can happen in the
API on backup related actions, this patch removes those windows of
opportunity using compare-and-swap for DB updates.

Races have been removed in following actions:

- delete
- create
- restore

Specs: https://review.openstack.org/232599/

Implements: blueprint cinder-volume-active-active-support
Closes-Bug: #1469659
Change-Id: I802bdf1ec8231e7fa0aece44106eba1a83f1d046

commit_message:
Add ddt to tempest venv

Some tempest tests, including those for neutron, require ddt.
This patch ensure ddt exists in the tempest venv.

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-08-24 15:43:09.000000000', 'message': 'add local_settings template for Ocata

ceilometer_policy.json file was removed as a part of
20ea82b9efe78516286c4b35c5dc644b296b4313 horizon commit made before the
Ocata release due to ceilometer API deprecation.

Having this in a template for Ocata results in an error on first login
via a given http server.

Therefore, this change adds another template for Ocata+ which does not
contain a reference to that file in POLICY_FILES.

Change-Id: I3320622684c3185db45094563f277d4c7ce0694d
Closes-Bug: 1712617
(cherry picked from commit d5072e4030d9f597cdb696a379f5ace9dadb8705)
'}]
commit_message:
add local_settings template for Ocata

ceilometer_policy.json file was removed as a part of
20ea82b9efe78516286c4b35c5dc644b296b4313 horizon commit made before the
Ocata release due to ceilometer API deprecation.

Having this in a template for Ocata results in an error on first login
via a given http server.

Therefore, this change adds another template for Ocata+ which does not
contain a reference to that file in POLICY_FILES.

Change-Id: I3320622684c3185db45094563f277d4c7ce0694d
Closes-Bug: 1712617
(cherry picked from commit d5072e4030d9f597cdb696a379f5ace9dadb8705)

commit_message:
Warn the admin of a potential OVS firewall_driver misconfiguration

OVS trunks work only with OVS firewall to implement security
groups. If a trunk request is indeed processed by an OVS agent
whose firewall_driver = iptables_hybrid, we should at least
log a warning to alert the admin.

Closes-bug: #1669074

Change-Id: I60e77e60e5e6d46ceff4bff61cbc07b6534ef152

commit_message:
Enforce ethertype with IPv6 integer protocols

By extending the black list to include the integer representation
for IPv6 we can succesfully block api requests to create security
group rules for IPv6 protocols with ehtertype IPv4.

Closes-Bug: #1706229
Change-Id: I5abeff178b3be18f1e93d00d9d546147b11c1a74

[{'created': '2017-08-24 06:11:55.000000000', 'message': 'scripts: scripts-library.sh: Fix location for log directory

The AIO job did not collect any logs from the host probably because
the GATE_LOG_DIR was pointing to the wrong location.
The $(dirname $0/../logs) was actually storing the logs in the
scripts/ directory instead of the root one so we need to fix that.

Change-Id: I17cc321ab640da4e251d21a996b537bda8cb3c1d
'}, {'created': '2017-08-24 15:21:34.000000000', 'message': 'scripts: scripts-library.sh: Fix location for log directory

the GATE_LOG_DIR was pointing to the wrong location due to a pushd/cd
that happened at another level.

Change-Id: I17cc321ab640da4e251d21a996b537bda8cb3c1d
'}, {'created': '2017-08-25 05:42:51.000000000', 'message': 'scripts: scripts-library.sh: Fix location for log directory

The AIO job did not collect any logs from the host because the working
directory was changing due to pushd commands and the logs were placed
into the wrong location. We already have the root location in the
OSA_CLONE_DIR variable so lets use that and only try to detect it if
that variable is empty for whatever reason.

Change-Id: I17cc321ab640da4e251d21a996b537bda8cb3c1d
'}]
commit_message:
scripts: scripts-library.sh: Fix location for log directory

The AIO job did not collect any logs from the host because the working
directory was changing due to pushd commands and the logs were placed
into the wrong location. We already have the root location in the
OSA_CLONE_DIR variable so lets use that and only try to detect it if
that variable is empty for whatever reason.

Change-Id: I17cc321ab640da4e251d21a996b537bda8cb3c1d

commit_message:
[placement] Disambiguate resource provider conflict message

When creating a resource provider, if the uuid or name (or both)
of the resource provider is already being used a 409 response is
returned. Prior to this change the error message always mentioned
the name of the resource provider, even if it was not the cause of
the duplication. That's misleading and unfriendly.

The new code will list the field and the value of the field that
was duplicated. From looking at the olso_db code that creates a
DBDuplicateEntry it appears that sometimes, but not always, the
exception could list both fields, so allowance for that is made
in the message output and the related gabbi tests.

Because this changes the error message, but not the error response
code, this does not violate the api interoperability guidelines[1],
so I'm willing to say this doesn't require a microversion, and thus
does not require a spec.

[1] http://specs.openstack.org/openstack/api-wg/guidelines/api_interoperability.html
If we do think this is a violation, then the guideline should be
made more explicit.

Change-Id: Ibafbfd8302977a2b4e9250fbb5ada283b69d3c25
Closes-Bug: #1693349

[{'created': '2017-08-24 14:09:59.000000000', 'message': 'Only report errors when collecting logs

Currently there are a lot of log collection lines
showing which files are not copied because they
are symlinks. They take up an awful lot of room
in the console log and are not very useful.

This patch sets the --quiet flag so that only
errors show up in the console log.

Change-Id: I2e03bf3f0a5b1aff3c4cc6a4e4803d172dabde65
(cherry picked from commit b161566a82a16c95b81a0c753939cbc68f098183)
'}]
commit_message:
Only report errors when collecting logs

Currently there are a lot of log collection lines
showing which files are not copied because they
are symlinks. They take up an awful lot of room
in the console log and are not very useful.

This patch sets the --quiet flag so that only
errors show up in the console log.

Change-Id: I2e03bf3f0a5b1aff3c4cc6a4e4803d172dabde65
(cherry picked from commit b161566a82a16c95b81a0c753939cbc68f098183)

commit_message:
Implement permission changes during rsync

In order to ensure that the files and directories
that are gathered for logs are readable for the
rename and gzip processes, we ensure that the
permissions and ownership are set during the copy
handled by rsync.

The previous method resulted in the files being
copied, but some files not being writable when
executing mv/gzip. This was noticed in the
os_neutron role where the calico job was failing
due to permissions issues for the felix config
files in the container /etc directory.

Change-Id: I7b84e0db25f44842a88315cd413ac39f75f9f8b9
(cherry picked from commit 0426d7f51b5bea9f7dc2baf3c3401565d016ba47)

commit_message:
gate-fix: Do not set ovsdb_connection as attribute

Due to the structure of the ovsdbapp classes, there is no need to set
the ovsdb_connection attribute. It is enough to pass it to the
constructor. Setting it confuses the ovsdbapp code and causes the
connection to not be started.

Change-Id: Ie0383216f829b3ea7a491712432a26789448ffa2

commit_message:
Add "default" rule when generate policy.yaml.sample

When we use tox to generate "policy.yaml.sample", the "default" rule is not
included in the file. When I try to use "policy.yaml" generated by nova
as the horizon nova policy rules. Horizon can not work for admin->Instances
panel. It is because rule "compute:get_all" is not included in "policy.yaml".
The "default" rule is enforced when a requested rule is not found.

Closes-Bug: #1703066

Change-Id: I14aeda3cd68ebc852e94fad475d0dd4cb71b662a

Copy inner content of tripleo-heat-templates

inside the tht_dir folder. Ensure we only copy the content
inside the directory to the right target path.

for avoiding conflicts.

commit_message:
Correct the "dns_domain" option by default

The "dns_domain" option needs to end in a "." to have a proper DNS name.
This change adds the sinle period and quites the string.

Change-Id: I000137b4071ea9ee2fae00eef7dfa4fa9fcadf3e
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
tests: bootstrap-host: Use btrfs tools to determine available disk space

df does not produce accurate results on btrfs filesystems so we need to
use the btrfs specific tools to get the available disk space.

Link: https://btrfs.wiki.kernel.org/index.php/FAQ#How_much_free_space_do_I_have.3F
Change-Id: I4f64b2c1d83342e9bfc0dcf1e417a00b6ca2f6ad

commit_message:
scripts: bootstrap-ansible: Add required packages on openSUSE Leap

Add support for installing required packages on openSUSE hosts.
Moreover, we force python2 on openSUSE since the shipped python-3.4
is not supported by Ansible upstream.

Link: https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/24180
Change-Id: I4ce2a066a32cf7a3b552f30788fe2c73511f99d0

[{'created': '2017-08-25 06:35:47.000000000', 'message': 'Remove usage of parameter enforce_type

Oslo.config deprecated parameter enforce_type and change its default
value to True in Ifa552de0a994e40388cbc9f7dbaa55700ca276b0. Remove the
usage of it to avoid DeprecationWarning: "Using the 'enforce_type'
argument is deprecated in version '4.0' and will be removed in version
'5.0': The argument enforce_type has changed its default value to True
and then will be removed completely."

Change-Id: I10004956f316247cf11d0e715ff11121852902d6
'}]
commit_message:
Remove usage of parameter enforce_type

Oslo.config deprecated parameter enforce_type and change its default
value to True in Ifa552de0a994e40388cbc9f7dbaa55700ca276b0. Remove the
usage of it to avoid DeprecationWarning: "Using the 'enforce_type'
argument is deprecated in version '4.0' and will be removed in version
'5.0': The argument enforce_type has changed its default value to True
and then will be removed completely."

Change-Id: I10004956f316247cf11d0e715ff11121852902d6

commit_message:
Add stunnel

In order to configure tls for redis, we need to use stunnel to handle
the encryption.

Change-Id: If239144185ae398932ea897d6ad4d657a1044572
Related-Blueprint: tls-via-certmonger

commit_message:
Disable encrypted volume in the tempest-deployer-input.conf

We are not deploying with encrypted volume support,
at least not in tempest's view point.

We do not have barbican support,
and the fixed_key manager is kind of deprecated anyway.
rbd support also missing.

See also:
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1383377
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1294422

Change-Id: I5cb308bd4f2391e82489acfa056fc699b3355f68

1. Change comments to make it clear that proxy_env_url is used by
apt-cacher-ng and must always be set when an http proxy is required.

2. Add keystone hosts to no_proxy list in deployment env vars

up.

Change-Id: If147754f3ddd7727f17e8c33e5a0583ab87ffacc
(cherry picked from commit 1b7628b3666e3b8dfd70e04f27e5954b44a318b1)
'}]
commit_message:
Improve proxy vars in user_variables.yml

1. Change comments to make it clear that proxy_env_url is used by
apt-cacher-ng and must always be set when an http proxy is required.

2. Add keystone hosts to no_proxy list in deployment env vars
because os_keystone role tests this addess to check services are
up.

Change-Id: If147754f3ddd7727f17e8c33e5a0583ab87ffacc
(cherry picked from commit 1b7628b3666e3b8dfd70e04f27e5954b44a318b1)

commit_message:
Exclude /etc directories properly

This patch fixes a bug where some directories in /etc were not being
excluded properly. It wasn't working because directories like
'/etc/selinux' weren't under /proc/$PID/root/etc and rsync wouldn't
exclude them.

Change-Id: I3aab89a7cc86964daae436594f60131e3b7549b3

> Hi Kien,

 > try:
 > client = {
 > '1': client_v1,
 > }[api_version.ver_major]
 > except KeyError:
 > client = client_v1

 > to use another endpoint other that v1.

Hi Kevin, I remove it because I use zunclient.client.Client, it will check the version, define api version then call to Client with matched version [1] (For now, we have only 1 version so it will be zunclient.v1.client.Client).

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/494967/5/zunclient/client.py"}, {'account_id': 22406, 'date': '2017-08-25 06:50:51.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

- option 2. Change zunclient.shell, call experimental_client if experimental = True else call zunclient.client.Client.

Both ways would work, I think.'}, {'account_id': 22076, 'date': '2017-08-25 08:49:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

[{'created': '2017-08-25 00:35:24.000000000', 'message': "Restrict partprobe to the device we just made partitions on

Trusty-era partprobe doesn't understand the iso9660 configdrive
partition on RAX hosts, and exits with a failure ([1] is somewhat
related).

 root@ubuntu-trusty-rax-iad-10622304:~# sudo partprobe /dev/xvdd
 Error: /dev/xvdd: unrecognised disk label
 root@ubuntu-trusty-rax-iad-10622304:~# echo $?
 1

Restrict the partprobe to the device with the new partitions

[1] https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/parted/+bug/1312277

Change-Id: If48b26f339a09231a65b518cb41af8e319250905
"}]
commit_message:
Restrict partprobe to the device we just made partitions on

Trusty-era partprobe doesn't understand the iso9660 configdrive
partition on RAX hosts, and exits with a failure ([1] is somewhat
related).

 root@ubuntu-trusty-rax-iad-10622304:~# sudo partprobe /dev/xvdd
 Error: /dev/xvdd: unrecognised disk label
 root@ubuntu-trusty-rax-iad-10622304:~# echo $?
 1

Restrict the partprobe to the device with the new partitions

[1] https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/parted/+bug/1312277

commit_message:
Fix ordering of swift3 in middleware pipeline

Beginning with commit 6ffcc29 of swift3, the swift3 and s3token middlewares
must come between authtoken and keystoneauth in the swift proxy pipeline.

When 6ffcc29 was committed, reordering was optional at the expense of an
unneceessary call to keystone.  However, the change becomes mandatory when using
keystone v3 tokens.  Without this change, authtoken will strip the necessary
headers that s3token just added to the environment.

Change-Id: Ic7d07d869aa617ee00190a9aedf411017539b97b
(cherry picked from commit 8b2fc7afc7563e475c67e95cf47a800ab2f5108c)

commit_message:
vars: suse: Add ca-certificates-mozilla package in LXC image

Ever since we stopped installing recommended packages in the LXC images
(I4d373346cf85ca037f1520058f6a3bce18489e3c) things started to fall
apart because we are missing the certificates provided in the
ca-certificates-mozilla package. As such, add it to the list of
recommended packages. This fixes the following error which only
occurs inside a container:

2017-08-24 11:06:47.346515 | fatal: [infra1]: FAILED! => {"attempts": 5,"changed": false, "failed": true, "msg": "Failed to validate the SSL
certificate for bootstrap.pypa.io:443. Make sure your managed systems have a valid CA certificate installed. You can use validate_certs=False
if you do not need to confirm the servers identity but this is unsafe and not recommended. Paths checked for this platform: /etc/ssl/certs,
/etc/pki/ca-trust/extracted/pem, /etc/pki/tls/certs, /usr/share/ca-certificates/cacert.org, /etc/ansible. The exception msg
was: [SSL: CERTIFICATE_VERIFY_FAILED] certificate verify failed (_ssl.c:661)."}

Change-Id: I857ffc350b5164630589c286b661304606e12f95
